  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improved marketing of coffee</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">company assessment of Meru Central Coffee Co-operative Union (MCCCU) was conducted in last week of September 2014. 

From the information gathered, MCCCU are into a business strategy to mill the Meru
County coffee, market it in bulk and preferably sell it directly to the overseas and local
buyers in a bid to get better prices for the farmer. In this mission, they united with
Meru North Farmers Co-operative Union and the Coffee estates to jointly manage Meru
County Coffee Millers Union (MCCMU), through a mill they have leased from Kenya
Planters Co-operative Union (KPCU). The Meru County government is in full support of
this initiative.

Based on the observations, interviews, focus group discussions and analysis of the
data, the mission team concludes that MCCCU meets Agriterra&#x2019;s minimum criteria
for partnership.

Therefore a partnership was started up and jointly an action plan for 2015 was elaborated.

Action plan for 2015 is for 6 months, to enable to get acquainted with each other and to able to sharpen the cooperation for 2nd half of 2015. 

In this action plan, we will focus on reviewing strategic plan 2012 &#x2013; 2017 for Meru Central Coffee Cooperative Union (MCCCU) and update strategic plan for 2015-2018, including SMART objectives and financial forecast.

At the same time, elaborate a well-structured business plan and marketing plan for Meru County Millers Cooperative Union (MCMCU), involving all relevant stakeholders. It is important to include all stakeholders to discuss first draft of business plan. 

See for more details the action plan.

Business plan and marketing plan elaborated.</narrative>
  </description>
